6:{"id":"gdp-growth","categoryId":"gdp","title":"GDP Growth Rate (Quarter-on-Quarter)","value":"0.4%","rawValue":0.4,"unit":"%","change":0.1,"changeLabel":"from Q3 2025","trend":"up","description":"South Africa's real GDP grew 0.4% quarter-on-quarter in Q4 2025, seasonally adjusted and annualised, above expectations of 0.3%. This marked the fifth consecutive quarter of expansion. Finance led growth (+1.4%), while manufacturing was the largest drag (-0.6%). For the full year 2025, GDP rose 1.1% — the strongest annual growth since 2022.","source":"$7","lastUpdated":"2026-03-10","series":"$8"}
